<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Apple engineers were working on Tuesday night to repair widespread outages across their systems, affecting iCloud, the App Store and Apple TV, among other services.</p>

<p>It was not clear what was causing the disruption, first reported around 8pm EST on Tuesday. </p>

<p>Apple's dashboard, showing the status of their services, was alight with red warning signs, indicating outages.</p>

<p>Apple's dashboard on Tuesday was showing outages across the system </p>

<p>Apple TV, Apple Arcade, Apple Books, Apple TV, iCloud and iTunes were just some of the services affected.</p>

<p>Some by Tuesday evening had already been repaired - two Apple Cash apps - and others were unaffected, such as Siri, Apple Maps and iMessage.</p>
